  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The solver pipeline is built on a multi-threaded finite-volume CFD kernel with a Python-based hemolysis post-processor; all validation runs report nominal completion with converged residuals. One isolated mesh-import crash was noted in an early pre-release build and resolved; no further fault-mode testing was performed against the production solver.",
