      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for the primary quantity of interest (volume-averaged shear stress) at the nominal operating point.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels yielded GCI = 1.4% for volume-averaged shear stress and GCI = 2.1% for NIH at 5 L/min / 3500 RPM. The medium mesh (5.8 M cells) was selected for the production sensitivity sweep, providing adequate accuracy at tractable computational cost. Discretization error is assessed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
